  "identifier": "Sensor",
  "description": " Provides a suite of tools for creating, transforming, and validating metadata about sensors, their components, and their manufacturers. The workflow starts from tabular data (e.g., Excel) describing sensors and produces SensorML files for both sensor systems and components, RDF/Turtle files for sensor types and instances, and RDF records for manufacturers. The package ensures compliance with the SOSA/SSN ontology, FOAF, PROV, DCAT, and PIDINST schemas, allowing integration with FAIR data catalogues and triple stores such as Apache Jena Fuseki. Each generated RDF/Turtle file is automatically validated for structural consistency and ontology compliance using rdflib. The overall solution supports the generation of HTML landing pages via XSLT transformations and follows the latest SOSA/SSN specifications (W3C 2017 and October 2025 drafts). The package is also aligned with the PIDINST schema (https://docs.pidinst.org/en/latest/white-paper/metadata-schema.html) and, through this, with the DataCite Metadata Schema 4.4. An example of a compliant SensorMLâ€“PIDINST implementation is available at https://linkedsystems.uk/system/instance/TOOL0022_2490/current/.",
